OL,3,CCompany fined #90,000 after worker
OL,4,Cdies from falling 20-feet through roof
OL,6,FThe work was not properly organised,
OL,7,Fplanned, appropriately supervised or
OL,8,Fcarried out in a safe manner and the
OL,9,Femployees were not trained for working
OL,10,Fat height when the incident occurred,
OL,11,Fthe trial heard.
OL,13,FSurface Technik (Old Hill) Limited
OL,14,Fformerly of Deepdale Lane, Dudley was
OL,15,Ffound guilty by a jury of a breach of
OL,16,FSection 2 (1) of the Health and Safety
OL,17,Fat Work etc. Act 1974.
OL,19,FThe company has been fined #90,000 and
OL,20,Fordered to pay costs of #28,956.
