OL,3,CCompany fined #90,000 after worker
OL,4,Cdies from falling 20-feet through roof
OL,6,FRobert Hammond, of Sutton Coldfield,
OL,7,Faccepted that he did not take
OL,8,Freasonable care for the health and
OL,9,Fsafety of both employees when he
OL,10,Fpleaded guilty to breaching Section 7
OL,11,Fof the Health and Safety at Work etc.
OL,12,FAct 1974.
OL,14,FMr Hammond was fined #8,500 and must
OL,15,Fpay the same amount in costs.
OL,17,FSpeaking after the hearing, HSE
OL,18,Finspector Sarah Smewin said "Working
OL,19,Ffrom height remains a leading cause of
OL,20,Fworkplace death and injury.
